{
  "_meta": {
    "description": "King Wen sequence (1-64) to 6-line binary hexagram mapping for The Recursive I Ching's Path Caster (docs/DESIGN-path-caster.md). This is the one load-bearing lookup for all Hamming-distance / changing-line math in caster.html — every consumer should read from here rather than re-deriving it.",
    "convention": "Bottom-to-top. Character index 0 (leftmost) = Line 1 (bottom line of the hexagram); index 5 (rightmost) = Line 6 (top line). '1' = yang/solid, '0' = yin/broken. This matches the Fu Xi/Shao Yong binary-sequence convention (line 1 = least significant bit) and the i-ching-summarized grammar's own 'Line 1'..'Line 6' section keys (Line 1 = binary[0]).",
    "how_this_was_built": "Recomputed from this repo's own grammars/i-ching-summarized/grammar.json metadata.trigram_above / metadata.trigram_below fields (NOT from that file's own metadata.binary field — see caveat below), using the standard trigram-to-3-bit mapping confirmed via WebSearch (2026-07-08): Qian/Heaven=111, Kun/Earth=000, Zhen/Thunder=100 (eldest son, yang at bottom), Kan/Water=010 (middle son, yang in middle), Gen/Mountain=001 (youngest son, yang at top), Xun/Wind=011 (eldest daughter, yin at bottom), Li/Fire=101 (middle daughter, yin in middle), Dui/Lake=110 (youngest daughter, yin at top). binary = trigram_bits[lower] + trigram_bits[upper].",
    "caveat_the_grammar_own_binary_field_has_bugs": "grammars/i-ching-summarized/grammar.json's own metadata.binary field was cross-checked against its own trigram_above/trigram_below fields for all 64 hexagrams and DISAGREED in 5 places: hexagrams 15 (Modesty), 16 (Enthusiasm), 46 (Pushing Upward), 63 (After Completion), 64 (Before Completion) -- the 63/64 pair's binary values were literally swapped with each other. Do not use that file's metadata.binary field for math; this table supersedes it. (The grammar file itself was left unedited -- its binary field is unused by the reader, only Judgment/Image/Line-N section text and symbol/pinyin/chinese_name are read from it.)",
    "verification": [
      "Self-consistency: recomputed binary bijects onto all 64 possible 6-bit values (0..63), no duplicates.",
      "Landmark check per docs/DESIGN-path-caster.md's own request: hexagram 1 (Creative) = 111111 (six yang), hexagram 2 (Receptive) = 000000 (six yin), hexagrams 11 (Peace, Earth-above-Heaven-below) and 12 (Standstill, Heaven-above-Earth-below) are exact bitwise complements (111000 / 000111) -- matches their famous classical relationship.",
      "Cross-referenced hexagrams 1-15 by name and binary (accounting for a bottom-to-top vs top-to-bottom mirroring between sources) against the independent adamblvck/iching-wilhelm-dataset (Wilhelm translation, GitHub, fetched 2026-07-08) -- names matched for all 15, and binaries matched for 13 of 15, with the 2 exceptions being exactly the two entries (15, 16) already flagged as buggy in this repo's stored metadata.binary, confirming the bug is in that field, not in this table's trigram-based reconstruction.",
      "Confirmed the trigram sons/daughters family (Zhen/Kan/Gen = eldest/middle/youngest son, one yang line at bottom/middle/top; Xun/Li/Dui = eldest/middle/youngest daughter, one yin line at bottom/middle/top) via WebSearch against general I Ching reference material, independent of this repo's own data."
    ]
  },
